content: I was looking for an app where I could do some simple technical drawings in. This app is what I was looking for however even I got the "pro" version of this app there is no undo option (or at least I can't find it anywhere in the app). This is a relative major issue as you need to go and delete the design created and start fresh all over hence the deduction of two stars as otherwise the app is just fab to work with. Add the "undo" feature and I happily will give 5 stars.

It's a great app! I love the non-stylus tapering for ballpoint pen based on "time the pen is on tension" rather then faultu pressure/velocity based tapering. Althoguh I love this feature, I think there should be an option to disable it on and off.

Pretty good. The built it help is great while learning. Not exactly sure what the point of a project is because you can't (that i can see) add pages. So project is a fancy word for "image". Copy and paste reduces image quality. And it doesn't look like you can add more white space/ make the canvas bigger.
Perfect app. Exactly what I needed. Above and beyond. 5 star in every way!!!
Excellent app. Just need to make it Microsoft and Apple compatible. Excellent job
so this is woderful to me
Best
I like it but it hard to understand how to use. VIDEO goes so fast and I can't get it. Maybe I so stupid...
Couldn't you have at LEASE had someone EDIT the instruction manual? It's the year 2020 and there are still NO standards for language translation? Hire an editor fer ferksake.
No stars could not open the program
Terrible app. Doesn't do as it says. You can't create dxf's . Fiddling around with awkward controls and trying to see the cursor under you finger. Isn't worth the money.

I've [tried] using this app for some time and I've had to give up, the controls are incredibly fiddly and the system often crashes or deletes projects. As many have said the free version might just be the better app! Unfortunate given that it could fill a gap in the app market and has potential, but the UI and general buggyness mean it's a no from me dawg.
Easy to use and works great on images
You have a good day now ya hear... Or so help me God I'll....
AMAZING!

I'm an engineer who goes to sites and do things and simple sketches at locations. We refuse to deal with the infrastructure carried in 3d capable applications. This app is close to exactly what we need with the mapping tool. Hope the developers keep at it. A real sp line tool and a mild snap to geometry seem a good step forward. The scale approach is difficult. If users are willing to put the work that most apps need, this one may hit the spot
Amazing app for those "got to get down on paper ideas" love the fact you can have measured designs too. NICE UI too and various options. Very good concept 100% effective.

(I would like to start off saying I don't have much in the way of CAD type training or experience but I wanted to try my hand with something 2d first.) This seems like it would be a good app, if it would stop crashing within minutes of opening/reopening. The free version doesnt seem to have this problem although I only used it for a limited time before purchasing pro. I really hope they fix this as it seems like it would be a good app for mobile use.

Once I got used to using the program I havent been able to stop lol its so much fun creating my designs for my woodworking projects! Take the time to learn it especially if youre a beginner its very easy once you get the hang of it! Great for basic projects I cant speak on more advanced work but give it a shot!
It could have more features, but overall not bad

There is no curve line tool. It shows there is a curve line tool but the app does not have one. I contacted the developer and they said there is a icon tool for the curve tool but it does not work and they have not added that yet. Seems a little deceiving.

The more I use it the better it gets. Once I understood it not a vector system (except entry) its fantastic and a new paradigm. Just wish you could make some tutorials videos with sound track and actual instructions.

Seems like a good app underneath but usefullness hidden by difficult navigation. I finally found the extended docs. Good so far. But the two 'tutorial ' videos are just ego tripping useless with obnoxious music. They only show what the speechless developer does for entertainment. Its vector draing is a weird since those objects cant be selected or moved once drawn. I guess this is why it NOT a vector app. Just vector input. There is no select tool. No move tool Cant change font size text

the app has potential, but is too buggy and frustrating to use. for instance, a very simple cad style drawing that would take 5min in autocad, takes an hour in this exercise in futility, because after that hour, it proceeds to delete your work and automatically overwrite your saved progress. Steer well clear.
will not allow you to make a knew sketch

great app! after a few hours of tinkering around you'll think you've got it! nope try again because this app is packed with features for $3!!! however there are two features id like to see implemented, such as a copy and paste tool to make multi dimension blueprints easier. and a tool to make edges of a rectangle convex or concave... and it may be that the app already has these and I just haven't found them yet ðŸ˜‚ otherwise, superb app! update: Apparently they didn't feel good taking my money lol
can you switch mm to inchs and feet? and how?
would love to have a blending tool for when you use pencils
FAIL - can't create a drawing because keyboard overlays the create dialog box. Tom Lipe, Maumelle, AR
How do I select items and then delete them in pro. You can select and copy but not select and delete...bummer!!

Adding the pen only mode made this product for me. I just used it to create a new design. I then went and removed all other drawing apps I was trying out. Love the app, still have a lot to learn but I can do the basics stuff, I can pick up new stuff as I go. Thanks
Please improve your app your app is not improving. We paid for your app don't stop updating.

So close to being a great app. Buggy, bad ui on some ways (pencil/eraser stays active while you are moving a text box around, so you end up scribbling all over the place)  NOT WORTH PRO at the moment (Dec 2017)  Otherwise, generally good ui, not taxing to hardware, very little lag.   I also wish I could buy a program with the same ui/features in a vector workflow.  (Galaxy Note 4)
The interface is not easy to familiarize with and overall th the app glitches  A lot
Good app for on site working. Or offine discussions  Thank you

This app has great potential, but the documentation is really limited (basically there is a short little icon guide and some youtube videos that are too fast to follow). Their ought at least to be a forum for asking questions. I have figured out most of it through trial and error, but how on earth do I start a new project or load an old one?

Great app! I'm an architecture student and found this tool to be incredibly useful! I particularly liked the integration of Google maps and quick demientions. I've been testing out several new apps for my work and this is my new default. Is there a way to change the units from metric to imperial? Thanks!
replyContent: Thanks for high score! There is not, but I can implement it in next update.

content: If icons were a bit bigger, it would be a 10 Star for sure.
Surprisingly easy to use, compared to others. Simply a great App for drawing or design. Five stars.
